    "narrative": "For LawDog\u2019s roster today, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (75.90) and **Bryson Stott** (71.93) headline our offensive output. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** remains our most reliable anchor in the #3 hole against Martinez, while **Bryson Stott** benefits significantly from a favorable park factor and a soft matchup against Mahle, providing the best efficiency profile on the board despite the threat posed by the opposing catcher\u2019s elite pop time. **Gleyber Torres** (67.52) also warrants attention; he is seeing a surge in value due to a massive SP skill edge against P\u00e9rez and a highly favorable BvP history, pushing him well above his baseline projection. **Jonathan Aranda** (64.56) is another standout, with the platoon advantage against Bibee providing the necessary boost to solidify his spot as a primary start at 1B.\n\nThe decision to bench **Matt Chapman** (44.35) was the narrowest call of the day. While **Matt Chapman** possesses the upside to exceed his 44.35 efficiency score, he was ultimately pushed out by the higher projected outputs of **Yainer Diaz** and **Gavin Sheets**, particularly as **Yainer Diaz** gains significant leverage from park factors. We are monitoring the status of **Will Smith**, **Lawrence Butler**, and **Gavin Sheets** closely; their scores are currently based on projected lineup spots. Should any of them fall lower in their respective batting orders once official lineups are released, their efficiency scores will see a downward adjustment. We are also proceeding with caution regarding **Tyler Freeman**, who faces a high-risk matchup against Burns; his score of 44.80 is marginal, and he remains a candidate to be swapped if we feel the need to chase stolen bases elsewhere, though our current configuration prioritizes the core efficiency of **Taylor Ward** and the lineup stability of **Daulton Varsho**.",
